# StudioVerse — Database Specification
**Version 2.0 | March 2026 | Classification: Confidential — Engineering Use**

---

## Preamble

This document supersedes all previous versions of the CoachingStudio Database Specification. It reflects the complete data model for the StudioVerse platform — a single-codebase, multi-tenant SaaS engine powering Coaching Studio, Training Studio, and Recruitment Studio from one unified Firestore database.

All collection names, field names, data types, relationships, indexes, and access rules defined here are canonical. Developers must not deviate from this specification without a formal document update.

---

## Section 1 — Design Principles

### 1.1 Core Principles

1. Firestore-first, NoSQL, denormalized for reads — Data is structured for fast reads, not relational purity. Denormalization is intentional and deliberate.
2. Studio-type tenancy — Every document that belongs to a Studio tenant carries a studioType field. Queries are always scoped to a studioType.
3. Separation of identity, organization, relationships, grouping, and execution — Users are separate from Companies, which are separate from Professional relationships, which are separate from cohort groupings, which are separate from assignments.
4. Assignment-driven architecture — Every resource (Program, Tool, Event) delivered to an Individual is mediated through an Assignment document.
5. userContext for RBAC — no runtime joins. Access control is precomputed into a single userContexts document per user.
6. Supports multi-tenant, multi-Studio, multi-Company, multi-Professional — The data model scales across all StudioVerse verticals without schema changes.
7. Audit trail on all critical actions — All sensitive mutations are recorded in the auditLogs collection.

### 1.2 Terminology Map (Data Layer)

| Data Entity       | Coaching Studio   | Training Studio     | Recruitment Studio     |
|-------------------|-------------------|---------------------|------------------------|
| studioType        | coaching          | training            | recruitment            |
| Role: professional| Coach             | Trainer             | Recruiter              |
| Role: individual  | Coachee           | Learner             | Candidate              |
| Role: company     | Coaching Firm     | Training Company    | Recruitment Agency     |
| programs          | Coaching Program  | Training Course     | Assessment Track       |
| tools             | Assessment        | Skills Evaluation   | Candidate Assessment   |
| cohorts           | Coaching Cohort   | Training Batch      | Candidate Pool         |
| assignments       | Coaching Task     | Learning Task       | Assessment Task        |
| reports           | Growth Report     | Completion Report   | Evaluation Report      |
| events            | Workshop          | Training Session    | Recruitment Drive      |

