## Section 3 — Detailed Schema Definitions

---

### 3.1 users
Purpose: Master identity record for every platform user.

| Field       | Type      | Required | Description                                                  |
|-------------|-----------|----------|--------------------------------------------------------------|
| id          | string    | YES      | Firebase Auth UID — document ID                              |
| studioType  | enum      | YES      | coaching / training / recruitment                            |
| name        | string    | YES      | Full display name                                            |
| email       | string    | YES      | Primary email address (unique per Studio)                    |
| roles       | string[]  | YES      | superadmin, company, professional, individual                |
| status      | enum      | YES      | pending / active / suspended / archived                      |
| avatarUrl   | string    | NO       | Profile image URL (Firebase Storage)                         |
| phone       | string    | NO       | Contact phone number                                         |
| timezone    | string    | NO       | IANA timezone string (e.g. Asia/Kolkata)                     |
| locale      | string    | NO       | Locale code (e.g. en-IN)                                     |
| isIndependent| boolean  | NO       | true if Professional with no Company affiliation             |
| approvedAt  | Timestamp | NO       | When SuperAdmin approved this user                           |
| approvedBy  | string    | NO       | SuperAdmin userId who approved                               |
| createdAt   | Timestamp | YES      | Account creation timestamp                                   |
| updatedAt   | Timestamp | YES      | Last profile update timestamp                                |

Notes:
- id = Firebase Auth UID. Never generate a separate ID for users.
- A user may have roles: [professional, individual] — e.g. a coach who is also a coachee.
- studioType scopes this user to exactly one Studio. Cross-Studio users require separate accounts.

---

### 3.2 userContexts
Purpose: Precomputed RBAC oracle document per user. Written exclusively by buildUserContext Firebase Function. Never written by the UI.

| Field                  | Type      | Required | Description                                              |
|------------------------|-----------|----------|----------------------------------------------------------|
| userId                 | string    | YES      | Firebase Auth UID — document ID                          |
| studioType             | enum      | YES      | Studio this context belongs to                           |
| roles                  | string[]  | YES      | superadmin, company, professional, individual            |
| companyIds             | string[]  | YES      | Companies this user belongs to                           |
| managedProfessionalIds | string[]  | YES      | Professional userIds this Company user manages           |
| myProfessionalId       | string    | NO       | This user's own professionalProfile ID                   |
| individualIds          | string[]  | YES      | Individual userIds this Professional manages             |
| cohortIds              | string[]  | YES      | Cohort IDs this user owns or belongs to                  |
| isIndependent          | boolean   | YES      | True if Professional with no companyId                   |
| isSuperAdmin           | boolean   | YES      | Convenience flag for SuperAdmin role check               |
| updatedAt              | Timestamp | YES      | Last rebuild timestamp                                   |

Rebuild Triggers:
- User created or role changed
- Professional added to / removed from Company
- Individual added to / removed from Professional's roster
- Cohort membership change
- Approval or deactivation by SuperAdmin or Company

---

