### 3.4 companyMembers
Purpose: Maps Professional users to their Company.

| Field     | Type      | Required | Description                                              |
|-----------|-----------|----------|----------------------------------------------------------|
| id        | string    | YES      | Auto-generated document ID                               |
| studioType| enum      | YES      | Studio context                                           |
| companyId | string    | YES      | Reference to companies.id                               |
| userId    | string    | YES      | Reference to users.id (the Professional)                |
| role      | enum      | YES      | admin (company manager) / member (regular Professional)  |
| status    | enum      | YES      | active / suspended / removed                             |
| invitedBy | string    | YES      | userId who invited this member                           |
| joinedAt  | Timestamp | YES      | When this member was added                               |
| updatedAt | Timestamp | YES      | Last status change timestamp                             |

Indexes:
- (companyId, status) — list all active members of a company
- (userId, studioType) — find which company a Professional belongs to

