### 3.9 programs
Purpose: Learning programs, training courses, or assessment tracks.

| Field             | Type      | Required | Description                                          |
|-------------------|-----------|----------|------------------------------------------------------|
| id                | string    | YES      | Auto-generated document ID                           |
| studioType        | enum      | YES      | Studio this program belongs to                       |
| title             | string    | YES      | Program display title                                |
| description       | string    | YES      | Full program description                             |
| coverImageUrl     | string    | NO       | Program cover image (Firebase Storage)               |
| tags              | string[]  | NO       | Searchable tags                                      |
| category          | string    | NO       | Program category / domain                            |
| createdBy         | string    | YES      | userId of creator                                    |
| ownerType         | enum      | YES      | platform / professional / company                    |
| visibility        | enum      | YES      | public / private / marketplace                       |
| isFree            | boolean   | YES      | Free access or paid                                  |
| price             | number    | NO       | Price in USD (if paid)                               |
| currency          | string    | NO       | ISO currency code                                    |
| moduleCount       | number    | YES      | Denormalized count of modules                        |
| estimatedDuration | number    | NO       | Estimated completion time in minutes                 |
| status            | enum      | YES      | draft / published / archived                         |
| createdAt         | Timestamp | YES      | Creation timestamp                                   |
| updatedAt         | Timestamp | YES      | Last update timestamp                                |

Indexes:
