### 3.16 assignments
Purpose: The core execution entity of StudioVerse. Every Program or Tool delivered to an Individual is an Assignment.

| Field           | Type      | Required | Description                                              |
|-----------------|-----------|----------|----------------------------------------------------------|
| id              | string    | YES      | Auto-generated document ID                               |
| studioType      | enum      | YES      | Studio context                                           |
| assignedBy      | string    | YES      | userId of the Professional or SuperAdmin                 |
| professionalId  | string    | YES      | Denormalized — same as assignedBy                        |
| companyId       | string    | NO       | Denormalized company context                             |
| userId          | string    | YES      | Individual's userId — one assignment per Individual      |
| cohortId        | string    | NO       | Source cohort (if created via cohort expansion)          |
| resourceType    | enum      | YES      | program / tool                                           |
| resourceId      | string    | YES      | Reference to programs.id or tools.id                    |
| resourceTitle   | string    | YES      | Denormalized title for display                           |
| status          | enum      | YES      | assigned / in_progress / completed / overdue / cancelled |
| deadline        | Timestamp | NO       | Optional completion deadline                             |
| assignedAt      | Timestamp | YES      | When assignment was created                              |
| startedAt       | Timestamp | NO       | When Individual first opened the resource                |
| completedAt     | Timestamp | NO       | When assignment reached completed status                 |
| overdueAt       | Timestamp | NO       | When assignment was marked overdue                       |
| notificationSentAt | Timestamp | NO    | When assignment notification was delivered               |

Indexes:
- (userId, status) — Individual's assignment list
- (userId, studioType) — all assignments for an Individual
- (assignedBy, status) — Professional's assignment dashboard
- (cohortId, resourceId) — duplicate assignment check
- (studioType, status, deadline) — overdue detection

